<br>
F8 has not worked on stationary mobs for two patches.<br>
<br>
F8 works if my monk pulls a mob to the group, then I can F8 target him.<br>
<br>
My guess is that whoever said it was due to the NPC not broadcasting its position, hit the bug square between the eyes.  Static mobs don't move, therefore do not broadcast their location.  Therefore, they are &quot;invisible&quot; to the code that F8 uses.  However, &quot;U&quot; uses a different technique to locate mobs, depending instead on the NPC graphic which is in the center of your screen, and then linking to the X,Y coordinates of that mob to determine what you are looking at.<br>
<br>
But that's just a guess.  Bottom Line Verant - You broke F8. <p><font size=2><select name="Furnok"><option>Furnok Shadowbane, 51 Rake of The Companions, Veeshan (W)</option><option>Seefull Goldeneyes, 51 Vicar of The Companions, Veeshan</option><option>Elbrynn Starglister, 50 Wizard of The Companions, Veeshan</option><option>Arowyn Starglister, 51 Illusionist of The Companions, Veeshan</option><option>Muldyrpike, 14 Bard of The Companions, Veeshan</option>
